comments: VanVleet (TOR) is in a legal guarding position and Beal (WAS) initiates contact to his head/face with his left arm.
Birch (TOR) runs alongside Beal (WAS) with a resting forearm to his side and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Johnson (TOR) establishes himself in Westbrook's (WAS) path and firms up on his right foot to absorb the contact.
Lopez (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in VanVleet's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact.
Birch (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
Westbrook (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Siakam's (TOR) body, which affects his ability to follow-through naturally on his driving shot attempt.
Lopez (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Siakam's (TOR) path and firms up on his left foot to absorb the contact.
Westbrook (WAS) is established in Siakam's (TOR) path and outside the restricted area, when Siakam releases his pass and delivers contact to Westbrook that dislodges him to the ground.
Lopez (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in VanVleet's (TOR) path and firms up on his left foot to absorb the contact.
Birch (TOR) jumps A to B into and makes contact with Beal's (WAS) body after the release, which affects his ability to follow-through naturally on his jump shot attempt.
Lopez (WAS) is in the paint for around three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Bertans (WAS) moves laterally into and makes contact with Siakam's (TOR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Johnson (TOR) makes clean ball contact to tie it up with Beal (WAS) and this occurs prior to a timeout request by the Washington bench.
Johnson (TOR) makes contact with Lopez's (WAS) arm, which affects his SQBR.
Hutchinson (WAS) has his arm extended out and marginal contact occurs as he removes it from Siakam's (TOR) path at the end of the drive.
Bembry (TOR) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Bertans (WAS) extends his legs out and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr. (TOR) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Lopez (WAS) is in the paint for around three seconds when he is imminently exiting as the foul occurs.
Bertans (WAS) moves into and makes contact with SIakam's (TOR) body, which dislodges him to the ground.

Birch (TOR) places a resting hand on Lopez's (WAS) arm and marginal contact occurs as he makes clean ball contact to tap the rebound away. Any contact between Lopez and Bembry (TOR) as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Bembry (TOR) mutually engages with Lopez (WAS) and incidental contact occurs as their legs get tangled during the rebound.
During the rebound, Lopez (WAS) and Birch (TOR) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Bertans (WAS) moves laterally into Siakam's (TOR) path and makes contact to his body, which affects his SQBR.

Replay review of the foul called on Lopez (WAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.
During the rebound, Birch (TOR) initiates contact by wrapping his arm around Lopez's (WAS) back and the contact affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Siakam (TOR) is in the restricted area when he makes contact with Beal's (WAS) body and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Gill (WAS) jumps alongside VanVleet (TOR) and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (WAS) stops his dribble by bringing two hands to the ball and then restarts his dribble.
VanVleet (TOR) moves into and brings his arm down to make contact with Westbrook's (WAS) arm and body, which affects his ability to make his intended pass.
Bembry (TOR) cleanly intercepts the pass and any follow-through contact with Gill (WAS) as they both pursued the pass is deemed incidental.
Westbrook (WAS) commits a take foul on Trent Jr. (TOR).
Neto (WAS) releases the inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Birch (TOR) makes contact to Lopez's (WAS) arm, which affects his SQBR.
Hutchinson (WAS) is late to the spot and still moving laterally when he makes contact with SIakam's (TOR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Neto (WAS) releases the inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Birch (TOR) briefly has his arm around Lopez's (WAS) back as he reaches to get to the ball, but the contact that occurs is marginal.
Bembry (TOR) makes contact with Neto's (WAS) arm, which affects his SQBR.
VanVleet (TOR) releases the inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Bertans (WAS) moves laterally into VanVleet's (TOR) path and makes contact with his body, which affects his SQBR.
Trent Jr. (TOR) commits a take foul on Mathews (WAS).
Hutchison (WAS) legally contests Siakam's (TOR) last second jump shot attempt.
